Economics of education adds economic dimension to the discussion of education systems and education policy. Topics covered during the course are: the benefits of education to individuals and society, including private and social returns to education, external effects of education and the effects of education on economic development, human capital and signalling theory, the provision of educational services, and the production of educational services.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of this course is to give students an understanding of different educational apsects as viewed by economists and basic knowledge of the application of economic thought in educational science.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  *understand theoretical concepts and trends central to economics of education, *are able to explain individual and societal effects resulting from education in the framework of economics of education, *are able to apply principles of education of economics on common issues of educational policy, administration and financing.
